
  Lunar Magi are the mages with the widest array of knowledge available
  to them.  They draw their power from the Moons, each moon has a 
  differant effect and each moon will give the caster certain spells 
  for them to cast.  For more info about the Moons and their powers,
  <lmhelp moons>.  

   Lunar Magi must remain disciplined at all times.  If a Lunar Mage
   should become chaotic, that Mage will lose all ability to cast
   spells.  As you may realize, it is to your advantage to have spells
   available to you.  Remember to maintain a positive ethics score.
   If you would like to know whether you are lawful or not, type <statme>.
   
   Lunar Magi have a wide variety of spells that they may draw upon,
   each one having a disctinct flavor and power.  For a quick list
   of spells and the Guild Level (gl) needed to cast them, see
   <lmhelp spells>.  For a full description, type <lmhelp> followed
   by the spell's name.  To report a spell idea to Duuktsaryth, use
   <lmspell> plus the idea.  However, only ideas that are in theme
   will be added.

   Lunar Magi have several unique emotions to represent the effects
   of having a reputation as a lesser magical guild.  For a full
   list of emotions, enter <lmhelp emotes>.  To contribute an idea
   to Duuktsaryth, enter <lmemote> followed by the emote.

   Spells fail.  Even the greatest of Mages can get unlucky.
   One of the unique aspects of this guild is spell failure.
   Once a spell fails, you will recieve a report of exactly
   what effect, if any, your spell has had.  To report
   an idea for a new failure message, please use <lmfail> 
   plus the idea.

   Communicating with fellow guild members is a very easy process.
   To say something to all Lunar Magi, type <lm> plus a message.
   To emote over that line, use <elm> plus a message.
   Example:  <lm Hi!>
    [Lunar] Duuktsaryth: Hi!
             <elm says Hi!>
    [Lunar] Duuktsaryth says Hi!

   Also, in order to help you to know who your compatriots are
   in the world, at any time you may type <lms> for a list of all
   Lunar Magi active in the world.  This will display their names,
   levels, guild level, and motto.

   In addition, upon reachin Guild Level 15 (Master Status), you
   will gain access to the Guild Master chat line.  This line
   can be used in th esame manner, except using the commands
   <hilm> and <ehilm>.

   The final command you must be aware of it <lmbug>.  This command
   will report to Duuktsaryth any erros you may find in the Guild.
   Please make use of this command if you feel that there is a 
   problem withe the guild code.  Remember that not all bugs produce
   a 'sensitive mind' message, they may just be a typo that Duuk 
   overlooked.  
  
   Enjoy your Guild.

   15-December-1995 					Duuktsaryth
